<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Male S3 and S4 broadly emarginated each with round patch of black bristles. Female paraclypeal and supraclypeal area with pale yellow marks, tibial scopa orange, T2 with some black hairs in anterolateral corners, process on S6 irregularly striate, not well defined posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Amegilla (Asaropoda) aurantia Leijs, sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.908.47375.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/376122" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">5L</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.908.47375.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/376122" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
